# Documentation Translation

- **Always translate documentation 1:1 from English to Chinese**.
- Every section, subsection, paragraph, and code example in `docs_espressif/en/*.rst` must have an equivalent in `docs_espressif/zh_CN/*.rst`.
- Do not skip, omit, or summarize content when translating.
- Maintain the same structure, heading levels, and formatting in both languages.
- Translate technical terms appropriately but keep code examples, settings names, and file paths identical.
- When creating or updating documentation, complete both English and Chinese versions before considering the task done.

```rst
// ❌ Avoid - Skipping sections in translation
// EN: Has sections A, B, C, D
// ZH: Only has sections A, C, D (missing B)

// ✅ Prefer - Complete 1:1 translation
// EN: Has sections A, B, C, D
// ZH: Has sections A, B, C, D (all translated)
```

